Brazil Stock Movers: Embraer, Banco Santander Brasil, Usiminas

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-08-25T14:39:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/brazil-stock-movers-embraer-banco-santander-brasil-usiminas.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:16 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index dropped 0.6 percent to 53,452.63.  Banco Santander Brasil SA (SANB11 BS) gained 4.3 percent to
14.50 reais. The Brazilian unit of  Spain ’s biggest bank plans to
buy back as many as 57 million units traded in Sao Paulo within
one year, according to a regulatory filing.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) declined 0.9 percent to 9.32 reais.
Delta Air Lines Inc. deferred an order of 100 small narrow-body
jets until 2012, delaying talks with planemakers such as
Embraer, the world’s fourth-largest.  Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais SA (USIM5)  (USIM3 BS) voting
shares dropped 3.3 percent to 23.50 reais.  Brazil ’s second-
biggest steelmaker sees little change in steel prices in the
third quarter compared with the second quarter, Chief Executive
Officer Wilson Brumer told investors today in Sao Paulo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
